"don't match."
msgstr "``program: '^science$' inlist $#genre` retourne `'1'`` si l'un des genres du livre correspond exactement à l'expression régulière ``^science$``, par exemple, `Science`, sinon ``''``. Les genres `Histoire des sciences` et `Science Fiction` ne correspondent pas."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:426
msgid ""
"``program: 'asimov' inlist $authors`` returns ``'1'`` if any author matches "
"the regular expression ``asimov``, e.g., `Asimov, Isaac` or `Isaac Asimov`, "
"otherwise ``''``."
msgstr "``program: 'asimov' inlist $authors`` retourne ``'1'`` si un auteur correspond à l'expression régulière ``asimov``, ex., `Asimov, Isaac` ou `Isaac Asimov`, sinon ``''``."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:427
msgid ""
"``program: 'asimov' inlist_field 'authors'`` returns ``'1'`` if any author "
"matches the regular expression ``asimov``, e.g., `Asimov, Isaac` or `Isaac "
"Asimov`, otherwise ``''``."
msgstr "``program: 'asimov' inlist_field 'authors'`` retourne ``'1'`` si un auteur correspond à l'expression régulière ``asimov``, ex., `Asimov, Isaac` ou `Isaac Asimov`, sinon ``''``."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:428
msgid ""
"``program: 'asimov$' inlist_field 'authors'`` returns ``'1'`` if any author "
"matches the regular expression ``asimov$``, e.g., `Isaac Asimov`, otherwise "
"``''``. It doesn't match `Asimov, Isaac` because of the ``$`` anchor in the "
"regular expression."
msgstr "``program: 'asimov$' inlist_field 'authors'`` retourne ``'1'`` si un auteur correspond à l'expression régulière ``asimov$``, ex., `Isaac Asimov`, sinon ``''``. Il ne correspond pas a `Asimov, Isaac` a cause de l'ancre ``$`` dans l'expression régulière."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:429
msgid ""
"``program: if field('series') != 'foo' then 'bar' else 'mumble' fi`` returns"
" ``'bar'`` if the book's series is not `foo`. Otherwise it returns "
"``'mumble'``."
msgstr "``program: if field('series') != 'foo' then 'bar' else 'mumble' fi`` retourne ``'bar'`` si la série du livre n'est pas `foo`. Sinon, retourne ``'mumble'``."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:430
msgid ""
"``program: if field('series') == 'foo' || field('series') == '1632' then "
"'yes' else 'no' fi`` returns ``'yes'`` if series is either `foo` or `1632`, "
"otherwise ``'no'``."
msgstr "``program: if field('series') == 'foo' || field('series') == '1632' then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` retourne ``'yes'`` si séries existe soit `foo` soit `1632`, sinon ``'no'``."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:431
msgid ""
"``program: if '^(foo|1632)$' in field('series') then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` "
"returns ``'yes'`` if series is either `foo` or `1632`, otherwise ``'no'``."
msgstr "``program: if '^(foo|1632)$' in field('series') then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` retourne ``'yes'`` si la série existe soit `foo` ou `1632`, sinon ``'no'``."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:432
msgid ""
"``program: if 11 > 2 then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` returns ``'no'`` because the "
"``>`` operator does a lexical comparison."
msgstr "``program: if '11' > '2' then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` `renvoie ``'no'`` parce que l'opérateur ``>`` fait une comparaison lexicale."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/template_lang.rst:433
msgid ""
"``program: if 11 ># 2 then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` returns ``'yes'`` because "
"the ``>#`` operator does a numeric comparison."
msgstr "``Program: if 11 ># 2 then 'yes' else 'no' fi`` renvoie ``'yes'`` parce que l'opérateur ``>#`` effectue une comparaison numérique."

